insert  into `commentanalysis`(`id`,`subject`,`comment`,`prate`,`nrate`,`sitename`) values (2,'positive','below is my review after using the phone since september 2016. after searching nearly for 15 days, resisting the chinese phones which offered a better configuration at lower prices, i settled for this model taking into consideration after sales and service and brand power. looks: gold one looks royal. phone back although made of plastic dosent slip from hands. light weight to carry. battery: battery is replaceable unlike chinese phones , so if the battery goes bad i can replace it myself than go to the service center. with 2g it lasted for 1.5 days. with 4g it lasts for a day. charging takes 2.5 hours. battery cable is short. ultra power saver mode servers is extremely useful when your battery is dying. memory: out of internal 16 gb , 10.2 is available, os and internal apps consume the rest out of 32 gb sandisk memory card 29.5 gb is available. both internal and external memory work fast, no lag while watching videos or listening to audio online and offline. the video streaming on 4g is good. screen: i put a affix tempered glass on the screen. screen touch works fine but could have been better . this isnt amoled display however i am satisfied with the tft display and its colors. checking phone in outdoor needs the outdoor setting to increase the brightness,it could have been better. camera: clarity of pictures from rear camera is good with size of an image to be 3-4mb. selfies from front camera have a wider selfie angle allowing more people to come in the selfie with fine quality. sound: sound during conversation is crystal clear. volte works. loudspeaker sound is okay. sims: i am using jio 4g on sim 2 and vodafone on sim1. both work seamlessly. heating: phone dosent heat after watching movies/videos for 2 hours both online and offline. i dont play games hence no comments on heating there. otg,blue tooth, hotspot ,wifi work. apps: phone dosent come with any basic apps like share it,facebook,whatsapp. but like chinese phones it isnt bloated with unwanted apps. notification indicator: the phone dosent have a notification indicator. this is a blessing in disguise for me as i dont wish to be bothered with pings/indications. the keys dont have a back light. there are only 3 keys and with the frequent usage of it you do come to know which key is where. voice recorder: useful for me to record lectures. my learnings: take screen shots by pressing the power button and home screen button simultaneously for 2 seconds when using 2g data pack ensure that in network selection only 2g is selected else mobile data hangs after some hours. memo is useful to type short notes. bad experiences: i returned the 1st phone. replacement came after 15 days. my friend ordered the same after seeing mine, she is satisfied too. update on december 13,2016: no issues till date. ...',3,0,'amazone'),(2,'positive','amazing phone under this budget segment. well assembled by samsung. gold one looks more pretty n classic than black..so i chose gold.. no hang issues..like erlier samsung phones.. its get more time for charging battery.. but once you have charged battery, theres no need to charge again on the same day',2,0,'amazone'),(2,'positive','its a gold for this price. this phone is really better from some phones like mi, lenovo, moto, etc. which claimed better functions. guys go for samsung either going somewhere else if you want a long life handset. it has volte. otg support. cameras are of best quality and its working is really good. its doest get hot after working for 4 hours regular on internet. battery works almost one day.',3,0,'amazone'),(2,'positive','at this price point this phone is good enough. but i didnt like the camera performance at all. samsung camera of 8mp so horrible, i just came to know. display quality of a picture or video is not too good. the phones build quality and look is awesome. if it suits your budget then obviously go for it. 2gb ram 16gb rom, 4g volte, front 5mp and back 8mp camera this is the best phone than moto e3 power. ive moto e3 but its lags so much since lenovo occupied it, moto is no more great quality phones at affordable price tag.',3,0,'amazone'),(2,'positive','was expecting gold color but ended up with silver.the metallic frame is sturdy even after unintentionally dropped from table.the camera clarity is superb.best for the price that i paid.the touch screen and the features provided are simply awesome.',5,0,'amazone'),(2,'normal','part time job without investment no registration fees. earn monthly 12000-25000 by working 2 hours per day. for more information type join and whatsapp us on this no. +91-8801234818',0,0,'amazone'),(2,'positive','i thought they delivered me on5 instead of on5 pro ;) the pic shown by amazon confused me, but when i checked the os (marshmallow), the internal 16gb storage and some other pics and features, i came to know that this is on5 pro. the phone is good in terms of specs at this price. but i am facing some battery issues with this device. even when i turn the brightness to minimum and enable the power saving mode and turn off the display, the battery still decreases by 1% in every 5 minutes. i am using jio sim and even when i am not using the internet, the battery still decreases very fast. some useful sensors are also missing. otherwise, this is a good device at this price range.',3,0,'amazone'),(2,'negative','have this is not a original back case .iam open the box and shock inside are black color film contains samsung label this is not original',0,2,'amazone'),(2,'positive','this a samsung product made to address the budget market. so it has the good characters of samsung and bad characters of a budget phone. what is good: looks impressive (i have a golden one) good charge retention (for my usage - average it comes for 2 days) no heating issues has data saver, power saver and ultra power saver mode ...all are practical features good call clarity touch operation is smooth no bugs (so far) samsung service centers not so good: extremely slow - its takes a long time to load any page over the net (sim change in a mi2prime gets much better results) slow in launching of contact names...generally very slow recommendation: for this price there are a couple of better choices. if you have decided on a good brand like samsung for the sake of service center availability, and decided on a sub 10k budget there are fewer better choices, but there are. buy only when you exhausted other options. if you find this review useful, please give your valuable feedback',3,0,'amazone'),(2,'positive','average smartphone nothing special pros:- android marshmallow os good camera but 8mp sensor only s-bike mode ergonomic design good build quality very good outdoor visibility no heating problems cons outdated processor missing gyroscope and ambient light sensors there is no hdr mode missing led notification light slippery design high sar values with 1.40 w/kg for head and 1.09 w/kg for body design and build - 6 display - 7 software - 6 performance - 7 gaming - 7 camera - 6 battery life - 7 value for money - 6 overall rating - 6.5',3,0,'amazone'),(2,'negative','worst phone ever.. delivered on 23 november nd it just fall from my hand nd with back cover nd temper glass its touch nd display is broke nd service center said that 5030 rupees for new touch nd display .. mi is much better than this .. its worth me of 11k with chinese touch nd display..worst mobile ever.. i will never buy any samsung product.. service centers also ask for more ..greedy peoples...',0,6,'amazone'),(2,'normal','my product is damage',0,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','good phone. extremely good phone, excellent t performance. battery backup was not expected , getting around 4.5 hrs of screen on time with moderate usage. go for it if you cant get the redmi 3s. heating issue solved after 2 updates.',4,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','everything is good abt lenovo k5 and along with amazon, great price great deal all things r good but delivery should be fast, bcoz if u place an order for a specific day then u have to wait for the delivery',3,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','i purchased this mobile lenovo vibe k5 during the great indian festival using my hdfc credit card and i am eligible to get 15% cashback. hope i get it too okay lets move on to the review- the phone was delivered in a nice package and that too 3 days before the expected arrival. i just love the amazon service. they are the best online shopping chain in india now i would like to answer most of the questions that might come into ones mind when thinking to buy the phone. q 1. why should i go for this phone when theres better known and loved xiaomi redmi 3 for the same price? ans- uhh..uhh...uhhh.. i would like to share my own experience with the most popular and best selling smartphone of 2016 - redmi note 3. i agree it has really cool features and good specs and all. the miui user interface is pretty great too, well let me tell you the version i bought was the 2 gb variant and its running good till now expect the really low available ram and really really bad device optimization. in my phone regularly i get available ram as low as 200 mb without any running application and some lite background apps. i have to keep restarting the phone every now and then to get more available ram and max it goes is 750 mb. well this is it. now about the vibe k5 the ram available is 1.1 gb as far now with the same background apps running. miui has many bugs that i encountered with the redmi note 3 and i expect the same to be the case with redmi 3. q 2. why am i posting only negative views about redmi 3? ans- well this question will certainly arise in your mind if you read the above answer. okay, i will answer to that too. actually i am giving an unbiased review of the phone and i am sharing my own experience. i clearly mean to convey lenovo is better on the software and optimization front. q 3. why not go for coolpad note 3? ans- actually both coolpad and lenovo are chinnese companies and they both are now well known in india expect lenovo is by far better in both terms of product quality and after sales service. you should anytime go for lenovo when you have a option those two. i havent used the coolpad note 3 so i cannot just tell about it. now for the real review - build: i would like to start by the build quality. it is just superb. i find the device nice to hold in the hand and literally its better than redmi note 3. the phone has a good grip but be sure to buy a back cover as you never know what might happen. hardware & software: this phone is powered by a snapdragon 616 octa core 1.5 ghz processor and runs on 2 gb of ram. also you get 16 gb internal storage(standard now a days) out of which 8.2 is available which not quite sufficient if you are a heavy user, so might consider getting the k5 plus which more ram and storage. on the software front the phone runs android lollipop 5.1.1 with vibe ui on top. you can anytime change to stock android launcher if you want. the screen is well lit and bright as well as responsive too. as i said before the hardware is really good and one of the best you can get in this price. one more thing you get dolby atmos speakers which pretty good and really loud (really). camera: this is the part where this phone lags and most other in this price range lag too. by lag i mean the picture quality is that good as one would want but anyways one should expect dslr like quality in a smartphone. the is on par with redmi note 3 i compared myself and found the color production was slightly better in the note 3. and about the video quality is fine too. recording is by default set to 720p if you want you can change it to 1080p. connectivity: having a removable battery this phone can accommodate 2 4g sims as well as a microsd card which is one reason its better than redmi 3. i dont like the hybrid slot stuff. sadly you dont get volte. gaming: many people must be thing about this too. well let me tell you, i tried some casual and hardcore games. the casual ones like angry birds 2 , subway surfers and most games out there work really well. but continuous gaming cannot be done on this phone due to the battery capacity. about the hardcore and graphic demanding games, well they dont run that good. i am not much of the mobile gamer, so this isnt a problem. heating: the most annoying thing that i face is heating with the redmi note 3 it goes upto 45 degree celsius during charging and idk why during normal usage too. i too a ton of relief when i found out this wasnt the case with vibe k5. battery: the phones battery is of 2750 mah capacity which is not that impressive but lasts for a day easily if you are a moderate user. continuous youtube and gaming drains the battery very fast. conclusion: my final thoughts are - this phone is a marvelous piece of hardware has a good design, hardware and features. and overall this phone is in my opinion the best you can get in this range. better go for it. you will really love the phone as i do. *****cheers*****',3,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','good ! its good and most speed and lot of games will paly at time',3,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','thanku amazon... this mobile is amazing.. n d camera quality is good... front camera is awesome.. display,sound everything is perfect..n sound is too good.. n main thing is that mobile looks great... bt didnt get headphones..',2,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','the phone was delivered within 3 days before the expected arrival. at the price range the phone specification is good. i buy two mobiles. its working fine. after 3 update 61mb, 48mb, 41 mb - hd voice (4g volte) enable. now i can call, direct without using jio voice app',3,0,'amazone'),(3,'positive','the product is good at this price point it is not the best if you are a music lover i would say go for this it will not at all dissapoint you the sound of the speakers are dolby speakers