cent, it supports dual sim with 4g, the vibe k5 plus doesnt have fingerprint scanner which very bad to see, even super cheap smartphones now days have fingerprint scanner. the 5 inch display has a resolution of 1920x1080p with 441ppi. the did is very decent, the touch is very smooth and responsive and the colors are good too. the viewing angles are ok not great because at certain angles the colors get washed out. the capacitive keys on the bottom are noy backlit and the notification led just lights up and does not blink like in other phones. -------------------------------------------------- -the performence- =================== the vibe k5 plus has the snapdragon 616 processor with adreno 405 gpu and 2gb of ram, the processor performs very well in general usage and also under heavy usage it performed well but in gaming there is a lot lagging in heavy games like modern combat 5 and asphalt 8. the vibe k5 runs on the android 5.1 lollipop and with the vibe ui on top of it, ui is just ok its not that great and also it does support lenovos theater max technology so you can use this for vr. -------------------------------------------------- -the camera- ============= the 13mp rear camera performs very well, its not that great like in moto g4 plus, but the images under natural lighting are pretty decent, the dynamic range is acceptable with nice contrast and color reproduction, but under artificial lighting the images were not that good. the camera does shoot video in 1080p which were ok, the front facing camera also performed just average. --------------------------------------------------- -the battery- ============== although the vibe k5 only has a 2750mah battery but it performed very well you can easily get a day with it under moderate usage but under heavy usage you may need to charge it before the day ends. the battery back up is not good as the redmi note 3 but its still very seeing it only has a 2750 mah battery where as the redmi note 3 has 4050 mah. the vibe k5 doesnt support quick charging so it takes around 2 hours to full charge it from 5% to 100%. ---------------------------------------------------- -the pros- =========== 1. decent built quality 2. decent display 3. nice camera 4. decent battery backup 5. theater max technology supported 6. decent speaker 7. sd card slot 8. removable back -the cons- =========== 1. no finger print scanner 2. only 2 gb of ram 3. no fast charging 4. ui not that good ---------------------------------------------- final verdict- the lenovo vibe k5 plus is a nice budget option for under 10000 rs. it is not good as the redmi note 3 or the coolpad note 5. but still a pretty decent option on a tight budget. ---------------------------------------------- if you like my review please support by clicking on that helpful button, it means a lot. ---------------------------------------------- thank you',2,0,'amazone'),(1,'positive',' the phone is slim and has a nice feel on your hand. it has an open able back cover which contains a removable battery 2 sim slots and a dedicated sd card slot. the phone is good for daily use and work its speed is good. only down side it is that it doesnt upgrade to 6.0',2,0,'amazone'),(1,'positive',' i already using my phone like a gun just keep keep shooting just like that bt this phone lenovo is total package n now its got volte support so i love this n thats why i bought this phone for my mother too',1,0,'amazone'),(1,'positive',' awesome work done by amazon . this is a excellent phone in budget , no issue till now. and the camera quality is good but in this range you cant get a better camera than this phone is having . i am happy to have it',4,0,'amazone'),(1,'positive',' its a beautiful phone from lenovo its ui very smooth very fast processing by its octa core processor and 2gb ram and ram management system also good always 1.2gb available for user out of 16gb memory 12 of user available display also sharp and nice like good design camera quality very good it can 