gold colour metal casing, model a6020a40 - pa2m0113in with 2gb ram, 16gb rom, 1.5 ghz octa-core processor, android 5.1.1 and all other specs and features were rightâ€¦. 13mp rear camera, front camera, dual speakers, twin microphones. most of the features were good except that, it was probably not volte ready and no guaranteed update to the next android version. the box contained the mobile phone, battery, a not-so-sturdy plastic cover for the glass, charger, usb cable cum charger cable, quick start booklet, warranty the battery was inserted and charged quickly .we inserted a micro sd card, took a couple of photos and it seemed good. the sample video and audio was played and it was also good. as i did not have micro-sim, i could not register use it immediately. as i am not a gaming fan no comments about it or any heating issue. a couple of days later, i got the sim and tried using the phone for its basic communication purpose. the major defect was that, the microphones were not working. i could hear the person at the other end loud and clear, whereas my voice was not heard even when i shouted. i tried using the voice recording feature and this also confirmed the problem that no sound could be recorded or reproduced. when an external earphone with mic was used, this problem was not to be found. so, i concluded that, the microphone or the associated noise cancellation features of the twin-mics was the culprit. thinking that, the above defect can be resolved, i searched on amazon for specific tempered glass protection, leather casing, 32gb data card and an earphone with mic for using with this product the service to resolve the problem, i chatted with amazon customer care to inform the same and was asked to download and run the smart-check app. meanwhile, i also contacted lenovo india support and got the local lenovo service contact details. although, i tried to reach them over the provided phone numbers, nobody was answering them. so, i personally went to the lenovo service center at rajajinagar, bangalore and explained the situation on 27oct2016. they suggested that, as this was from amazon, i should ask for a replacement, as the service center can provide service only and can assure about parts only until warranty exists ;rather, amazon could replace the product. this scared me a bit and i became sceptical as this created more worry in me, i called up amazon customer care using another phone and explained the problem over phone. i was suggested to use the smart check app. after downloading and installing the app twice, (which would run for a few seconds and then ask for a pin), i informed the same to the amazon customer care at around 1240h and they said someone from the mobile support team would contact me during my chosen time slot of 1300h to 1400h . however, by 1600h evening as i had not received call from the amazon mobile support team, i explained the problem once again. the customer support executive#1 asked not to disconnect the call for 8 - 10 min and tried to connect me to the amazon mobile-support team. as he could not connect even after 12 â€“ 15 min, he apologized and suggested that, he would place a replacement request on my behalf. i thanked him and asked for procedures to replace which he patiently explained. meanwhile, i sent a mail to amazon customer care to have a record of the same. after sometime at 1749h, i saw a mail response from amazon customer service consultant #2 stating that, due to the value of my order being rs.6999, they had some restrictions to create replacement and forwarded to his manager to create the replacement request on my behalf. the mail assured me that, as the return window is active until 04nov2016 and the product is available with the same seller, there will not be any problem with the replacement and would be updated within 24-48 hours. i started packing for the items in lenovo box with all accessories and was hoping for a defect-free phone this time. later at around 1840h, i got a